WEBVTT

1
00:00:33.951 --> 00:00:35.745
(RATTLING, CLANKING)

2
00:03:56.445 --> 00:03:58.447
Hey, this area's restricted.

3
00:03:58.531 --> 00:04:00.908
Oh, hi. Yeah, I know.
They called me down here.

4
00:04:00.991 --> 00:04:02.743
Some of this wiring got screwed up.

5
00:04:02.827 --> 00:04:04.245
Nobody called it down to me.

6
00:04:04.328 --> 00:04:05.954
I'm gonna have to see a work order.

7
00:04:06.038 --> 00:04:08.124
Yeah. Just a second.

8
00:04:11.627 --> 00:04:13.045
There you are.

9
00:04:13.712 --> 00:04:14.797
(GRUNTS)

10
00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:16.841
- (GROANING)
- Nothing personal.

11
00:04:20.261 --> 00:04:21.929
- (APPLAUSE)
- MAN: Well, I guess that wraps it up.

12
00:04:22.012 --> 00:04:23.305
Good work, everybody.

13
00:04:23.389 --> 00:04:25.015
(CHUCKLES)

14
00:04:25.433 --> 00:04:28.283
Marty, I couldn't be happier
with the way this worked out.

15
00:04:32.314 --> 00:04:34.442
- Congratulations.
- Good for you.

16
00:04:34.817 --> 00:04:36.485
(PHONES RINGING)

17
00:04:36.569 --> 00:04:39.113
- (ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)
- Oh, hold that.

18
00:04:39.196 --> 00:04:40.823
- Whoa.
- (WOMAN CLEARS THROAT)

19
00:04:42.074 --> 00:04:43.534
Gee, thanks.

20
00:04:44.535 --> 00:04:46.537
(CHUCKLING)

21
00:04:49.457 --> 00:04:50.708
(BELL DINGS)

22
00:04:52.209 --> 00:04:54.837
Thanks for pushing
that, Bob. The light's on,

23
00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:56.714
but you never know. It
really might be broken.

24
00:04:56.797 --> 00:04:57.923
Shut up.

25
00:05:07.808 --> 00:05:08.809
(WOMAN COUGHING)

26
00:05:13.063 --> 00:05:14.315
So remember, honey...

27
00:05:17.443 --> 00:05:18.486
(BEEPING)

28
00:05:20.529 --> 00:05:22.281
(ALL GASPING)

29
00:05:25.784 --> 00:05:27.578
(ALL SCREAMING)

30
00:05:31.916 --> 00:05:34.043
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

31
00:05:37.296 --> 00:05:39.548
- (SCREAMING CONTINUES)
- WOMAN: No! Please!

32
00:05:44.303 --> 00:05:47.097
(GASPING, PANTING)

33
00:05:51.852 --> 00:05:52.978
Ooh.

34
00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:55.773
Jesus.

35
00:05:56.148 --> 00:05:57.733
Bob, what button did you push?

36
00:06:04.990 --> 00:06:08.911
- (SIRENS WAILING)
- (HORN HONKING)

37
00:06:08.994 --> 00:06:11.872
(BYSTANDERS CHATTERING, SHOUTING)

38
00:06:13.290 --> 00:06:15.376
(TIRES SCREECHING)

39
00:06:24.927 --> 00:06:27.346
(RADIO CHATTER)

40
00:06:42.236 --> 00:06:44.321
WOMAN: Peter! Come on!

41
00:06:44.572 --> 00:06:46.615
Mr. Bagwell, make sure
these other elevators remain

42
00:06:46.699 --> 00:06:49.034
- locked down and empty.
- PETER: Yes, sir.

43
00:06:49.118 --> 00:06:50.744
Now, there's no other way, no doors...

44
00:06:50.828 --> 00:06:52.663
no other way in or out
except through access panels.

45
00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:53.831
- Is that correct?
- Yes, sir.

46
00:06:53.914 --> 00:06:55.958
All right, gentlemen, what we
have here are 13 passengers

47
00:06:56.041 --> 00:06:59.169
in an express elevator below floor 30.

48
00:07:00.504 --> 00:07:02.006
Bomb's already taken out cables.

49
00:07:02.089 --> 00:07:04.674
Bomber wants $3 million, or
he blows the emergency brakes.

50
00:07:04.758 --> 00:07:05.968
What's our clock?

51
00:07:06.051 --> 00:07:07.469
He gave one hour.

52
00:07:08.596 --> 00:07:10.973
That leaves us 23 minutes exactly.

53
00:07:11.140 --> 00:07:13.308
Anything else that'll keep
this elevator from falling?

54
00:07:13.392 --> 00:07:14.393
The basement.

55
00:07:14.476 --> 00:07:16.687
The city would like to avoid
that event, Officer Traven.

56
00:07:16.770 --> 00:07:18.230
We can't just unload the passengers?

57
00:07:18.314 --> 00:07:19.982
This is an express elevator, gentlemen.

58
00:07:20.065 --> 00:07:21.900
The only way in or out
is through access panels.

59
00:07:21.984 --> 00:07:24.069
Bomber's also wired the
hatch to trigger the bomb,

60
00:07:24.153 --> 00:07:26.703
which seats him in the
crazy but not stupid section.

61
00:07:27.448 --> 00:07:29.867
Sir, Harry volunteers
to examine the device.

62
00:07:30.909 --> 00:07:32.036
Yeah, right.

63
00:07:32.328 --> 00:07:34.705
Fine. The two of you check it out.

64
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:37.916
MAN: The nearest access panel's
on the 32nd floor in the lobby.

65
00:07:38.042 --> 00:07:40.293
MAC: I want reports only.
We're in a holding pattern.

66
00:07:40.377 --> 00:07:42.212
Worthy, Briggs, I want
you to secure the base area.

67
00:07:42.296 --> 00:07:44.840
No one in or out. Everyone else,
I want you to affirm building evac.

68
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:45.924
Move!

69
00:07:46.842 --> 00:07:48.218
Looks like we're walkin'.

70
00:07:50.054 --> 00:07:52.264
- MAN: Hurry, folks, but watch your step.
- JACK: Twenty-nine!

71
00:07:52.348 --> 00:07:55.184
MAN: All the way down
to the lobby! Let's go, folks!

72
00:07:55.893 --> 00:07:57.061
JACK: Thirty!

73
00:07:59.730 --> 00:08:00.731
Thirty-one!

74
00:08:03.317 --> 00:08:04.318
Thirty-two.

75
00:08:24.296 --> 00:08:25.547
(DRILL WHIRRING)

76
00:08:26.507 --> 00:08:27.799
- Hello?
- WOMAN: What's going on?

77
00:08:27.883 --> 00:08:29.301
MAN 1: Come on, man. Get us out of here!

78
00:08:29.385 --> 00:08:30.552
MAN 2: Hello?

79
00:08:30.636 --> 00:08:32.336
- WOMAN: What's that?
- MAN: Hello!

80
00:08:35.808 --> 00:08:39.144
- WOMAN: Please help us!
- (SHOUTING CONTINUES)

81
00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:52.741
(DRILLING CONTINUES)

82
00:09:05.504 --> 00:09:08.757
WOMAN: Help! Please! Get us out of here!

83
00:09:10.008 --> 00:09:11.051
Please!

84
00:09:34.324 --> 00:09:37.202
WOMAN: Please, get us out of here!

85
00:09:39.496 --> 00:09:41.165
MAN: Who's up there?

86
00:09:41.874 --> 00:09:44.293
Who's up there? What's going on?

87
00:09:44.626 --> 00:09:47.254
Ladies and gentlemen, this is the LAPD.

88
00:09:47.337 --> 00:09:49.465
- Thank God!
- What are you doing up there?

89
00:09:49.757 --> 00:09:52.217
JACK: <i>There has been
an elevator malfunction,</i>

90
00:09:52.301 --> 00:09:54.011
<i>so just relax.</i>

91
00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:56.013
MAN: Hey, come on!

92
00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:57.473
What are you guys waiting for?

93
00:09:57.556 --> 00:09:59.975
We'll have you out of
there as soon as possible.

94
00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:02.561
Am I lying?

95
00:10:03.771 --> 00:10:05.773
How come they sent cops here?

96
00:10:06.064 --> 00:10:07.775
Shouldn't they send repair guys?

97
00:10:08.192 --> 00:10:10.392
- WOMAN: Yeah.
- MAN: Doesn't make any sense.

98
00:10:16.617 --> 00:10:17.743
What do you think?

99
00:10:19.828 --> 00:10:21.628
You're the expert. I just work here.

100
00:10:21.789 --> 00:10:23.415
Looks pretty solid.

101
00:10:24.541 --> 00:10:26.835
- Anyone we know?
- I don't recognize the work,

102
00:10:26.919 --> 00:10:28.128
but he's a pro.

103
00:10:29.379 --> 00:10:30.756
Oh, he's cuttin' it close.

104
00:10:31.507 --> 00:10:33.842
- I don't like it.
- Yeah, well, what's to like?

105
00:10:33.926 --> 00:10:35.719
Mac said we hold, so we hold.

106
00:10:45.521 --> 00:10:47.356
HARRY: <i>All right, pop quiz.</i>

107
00:10:47.606 --> 00:10:49.691
The airport. Gunman with one hostage.

108
00:10:49.775 --> 00:10:52.175
He's usin' her for cover.
He's almost to a plane.

109
00:10:53.111 --> 00:10:54.738
You're a hundred feet away.

110
00:11:00.702 --> 00:11:01.703
Jack.

111
00:11:03.956 --> 00:11:05.290
Shoot the hostage.

112
00:11:06.250 --> 00:11:07.251
What?

113
00:11:07.459 --> 00:11:09.169
Take her out of the equation.

114
00:11:09.461 --> 00:11:12.511
Go for the good wound, and
he can't get to the plane with her.

115
00:11:12.714 --> 00:11:15.509
- Clear shot.
- You're deeply nuts. You know that?

116
00:11:15.676 --> 00:11:18.428
"Shoot the hostage." Geez. (CHUCKLING)

117
00:11:21.557 --> 00:11:23.141
Harry, this is wrong.

118
00:11:23.642 --> 00:11:25.185
He's gonna blow it anyway.

119
00:11:25.853 --> 00:11:26.854
Why?

120
00:11:27.813 --> 00:11:29.189
I don't know. Gut feeling.

121
00:11:29.398 --> 00:11:31.400
Well, right now, Mac outranks your gut,

122
00:11:31.483 --> 00:11:32.609
so we sit.

123
00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:35.279
This is taking way too long.

124
00:11:37.114 --> 00:11:39.157
How much you think that elevator weighs?

125
00:11:39.408 --> 00:11:41.243
Jack, come on.

126
00:11:43.537 --> 00:11:45.914
Maybe we can do something
about those hostages.

127
00:11:47.666 --> 00:11:49.316
We're not gonna shoot 'em, right?

128
00:11:51.420 --> 00:11:54.370
- MAN 1: Hey, where are you going?
- MAN 2: What's going on?

129
00:11:56.174 --> 00:12:00.012
WOMAN: Don't go! Don't leave us here!

130
00:12:14.776 --> 00:12:16.826
No, we just take them
out of the equation.

131
00:12:50.479 --> 00:12:52.940
- You sure it'll hold?
- It'll hold.

132
00:12:54.942 --> 00:12:56.193
Six minutes.

133
00:12:57.235 --> 00:13:00.405
I can't get any more
time. He's not talkin'!

134
00:13:00.489 --> 00:13:02.741
I need the goddamn money now!

135
00:13:13.001 --> 00:13:16.046
Tell me again, Harry.
Why did I take this job?

136
00:13:16.129 --> 00:13:17.965
Oh, come on. Thirty more years of this,

137
00:13:18.048 --> 00:13:20.592
you get a tiny pension
and a cheap gold watch.

138
00:13:20.759 --> 00:13:23.261
Cool. Whoa!

139
00:13:27.391 --> 00:13:29.101
(PANTING)

140
00:13:34.398 --> 00:13:36.566
(CLANKING)

141
00:13:44.700 --> 00:13:45.993
(GRUNTING)

142
00:13:54.960 --> 00:13:58.088
- God, it's hot in here.
- WOMAN: There's no air.

143
00:13:58.171 --> 00:13:59.756
Can't they just pry the doors open?

144
00:13:59.840 --> 00:14:01.091
WOMAN: I can't breathe.

145
00:14:06.346 --> 00:14:08.140
Don't fuck with daddy.

146
00:14:08.932 --> 00:14:12.310
(BEEPING)

147
00:14:12.436 --> 00:14:13.895
(SHOUTING)

148
00:14:15.147 --> 00:14:16.398
(SCREAMING)

149
00:14:20.569 --> 00:14:22.654
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

150
00:14:25.782 --> 00:14:27.951
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

151
00:14:30.746 --> 00:14:33.415
- (SCREAMS)
- WOMAN: Oh, my God!

152
00:14:34.875 --> 00:14:38.211
(CREAKING)

153
00:14:38.295 --> 00:14:41.214
- Oh, my God! What's happening?
- Grab her hand!

154
00:14:42.716 --> 00:14:44.801
Usually they fall down now.

155
00:14:45.177 --> 00:14:47.471
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

156
00:14:51.892 --> 00:14:53.143
Get her up!

157
00:14:54.019 --> 00:14:56.813
He's early. The son of a bitch is early.

158
00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:13.455
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

159
00:15:16.374 --> 00:15:18.293
Mac, we need more help up here now!

160
00:15:19.377 --> 00:15:22.964
Oh, please open the
door! I don't wanna die!

161
00:15:23.048 --> 00:15:24.341
Please save us!

162
00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:31.598
WOMAN: Open the door!

163
00:15:31.681 --> 00:15:33.433
Open the door! Please!

164
00:15:33.517 --> 00:15:35.310
- Save me! I wanna get out!
- MAN: Open the door!

165
00:15:35.393 --> 00:15:36.645
WOMAN: Let me out!

166
00:15:36.728 --> 00:15:38.897
- Please help me!
- Joan, get back!

167
00:15:38.980 --> 00:15:40.732
JACK: We'll get you out!

168
00:15:40.816 --> 00:15:42.901
- Give me your hands!
- That's it, go on.

169
00:15:42.984 --> 00:15:44.820
It's okay. Give me your hands.

170
00:15:44.903 --> 00:15:45.904
Pull me through!

171
00:15:45.987 --> 00:15:47.864
(METALLIC GROANING)

172
00:15:52.744 --> 00:15:54.162
(GASPS) Oh, God!

173
00:15:54.246 --> 00:15:55.997
Watch your head. Watch your head.

174
00:15:56.081 --> 00:15:57.958
- Help me!
- Okay, I've got you. I've got you.

175
00:15:58.041 --> 00:15:59.626
- HARRY: Take it easy!
- Oh, thank you!

176
00:15:59.709 --> 00:16:00.710
JACK: You're fine.

177
00:16:00.794 --> 00:16:02.671
- Oh, thank you.
- You're fine.

178
00:16:02.754 --> 00:16:04.904
- Take her. Let's go! Next!
- Lady, come on.

179
00:16:07.467 --> 00:16:10.762
- Thank you. Oh.
- I've got you, ma'am.

180
00:16:13.014 --> 00:16:14.599
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

181
00:16:14.683 --> 00:16:16.333
Just move back, please. Get back.

182
00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:19.688
What the hell is all this?

183
00:16:19.771 --> 00:16:21.314
- Help us! Hurry!
- (SCREAMS)

184
00:16:24.734 --> 00:16:26.862
MAN: Hurry up! Hurry up!
Let's go! Go! Go! Let's go!

185
00:16:26.945 --> 00:16:30.045
- JACK: Let's go! Let's go!
- HARRY: Come on! Come on! Come on!

186
00:16:34.161 --> 00:16:36.872
- Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
- HARRY: Come on.

187
00:16:36.955 --> 00:16:39.555
- Help me out! Please help me out!
- Watch your head.

188
00:16:41.418 --> 00:16:42.460
Come on, lady! Come on!

189
00:16:42.544 --> 00:16:43.920
- No. No.
- Come on, lady!

190
00:16:44.004 --> 00:16:46.298
- Come on!
- Grab my hand! Come on!

191
00:16:47.716 --> 00:16:48.967
Go!

192
00:16:49.050 --> 00:16:51.261
WOMAN: There's one
more. Can you pull her out?

193
00:16:51.344 --> 00:16:53.346
Come on. Come on, let's go!

194
00:16:53.430 --> 00:16:55.932
- No. No, I can't!
- It's going to fall.

195
00:16:56.141 --> 00:16:59.227
Just take one step, reach
out, and take my hand.

196
00:16:59.519 --> 00:17:01.438
- Come on!
- Hurry!

197
00:17:01.521 --> 00:17:02.814
Come on!

198
00:17:02.898 --> 00:17:04.733
(WHIMPERING)

199
00:17:05.442 --> 00:17:08.445
Oh, God! Don't let go of me!

200
00:17:08.528 --> 00:17:09.613
You're okay.

201
00:17:12.282 --> 00:17:14.075
(SHOUTING)

202
00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:24.211
Great God!

203
00:17:24.377 --> 00:17:26.838
- (ALL YELLING)
- Oh, my shoe!

204
00:17:26.922 --> 00:17:28.215
MAN: Let's go, let's go!

205
00:17:29.758 --> 00:17:31.218
JACK: Was it good for you?

206
00:17:31.426 --> 00:17:32.802
Oh, it was great for me.

207
00:17:32.886 --> 00:17:34.346
How was it for you, honey?

208
00:17:34.596 --> 00:17:36.306
- Elevator dropped.
- Oh, good.

209
00:17:36.389 --> 00:17:37.766
That's good to know.

210
00:17:38.975 --> 00:17:40.185
(BOTH SIGHING)

211
00:17:41.770 --> 00:17:42.938
Oh.

212
00:17:43.939 --> 00:17:45.190
Is your watch slow?

213
00:17:45.273 --> 00:17:46.733
Uh-uh. No, no. He jumped the gun.

214
00:17:46.816 --> 00:17:48.401
We had three minutes left.

215
00:17:48.610 --> 00:17:49.945
Why does he do that?

216
00:17:50.028 --> 00:17:51.863
He's losing his three million.

217
00:17:52.197 --> 00:17:54.997
I don't know. Maybe he couldn't
hold his wad long enough.

218
00:17:55.200 --> 00:17:57.702
It's a common problem
among middle-aged men.

219
00:17:57.786 --> 00:17:59.454
(SNIFFS) So I'm told.

220
00:18:04.918 --> 00:18:06.253
He's here.

221
00:18:06.336 --> 00:18:08.386
He could've blown
that thing from Pacoima.

222
00:18:09.631 --> 00:18:10.674
No.

223
00:18:11.132 --> 00:18:13.093
He knew we were up to something.

224
00:18:13.301 --> 00:18:14.761
He's close by.

225
00:18:14.844 --> 00:18:16.805
He's not gonna corner
himself in a building.

226
00:18:16.888 --> 00:18:18.932
We evacuated anyway. Come on.

227
00:18:21.726 --> 00:18:22.978
(SIGHS)

228
00:18:25.188 --> 00:18:26.356
All right.

229
00:18:27.565 --> 00:18:30.415
He'd want to be here, but
he'd want to stay mobile, right?

230
00:18:33.989 --> 00:18:35.365
The elevators.

231
00:18:35.991 --> 00:18:37.575
The passenger cars were stopped.

232
00:18:37.659 --> 00:18:38.759
They checked them out.

233
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:40.810
What about the freight elevators?

234
00:19:01.975 --> 00:19:03.643
(MAN COUGHING)

235
00:19:05.562 --> 00:19:07.856
Will the mystery guest please sign in?

236
00:19:08.064 --> 00:19:09.065
What?

237
00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:12.360
Jack.

238
00:19:13.486 --> 00:19:14.529
Damn it!

239
00:19:51.775 --> 00:19:53.526
- (GUNSHOTS)
- (GASPS)

240
00:19:56.237 --> 00:19:57.947
- Ah.
- Get to the floor!

241
00:20:05.205 --> 00:20:06.373
Ah!

242
00:20:08.792 --> 00:20:10.251
(GROANING)

243
00:20:11.669 --> 00:20:12.712
(GRUNTING)

244
00:20:14.422 --> 00:20:16.299
Shit! Shit! Shit!

245
00:20:18.676 --> 00:20:21.096
Up! Get your ass up!

246
00:20:21.179 --> 00:20:22.889
(GROANING)

247
00:21:04.347 --> 00:21:08.351
I don't suppose anybody'll
give me three million just for you.

248
00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:11.479
- (GUN CLICKS)
- (GRUNTING)

249
00:21:14.315 --> 00:21:16.151
- Hold it!
- Ah!

250
00:21:17.527 --> 00:21:19.446
Pop quiz, hot shot.

251
00:21:20.697 --> 00:21:22.240
Terrorist holding a police hostage.

252
00:21:22.323 --> 00:21:24.159
Got enough dynamite strapped to his chest

253
00:21:24.242 --> 00:21:25.743
to blow a building in half.

254
00:21:25.827 --> 00:21:27.245
