for that description.

821
00:55:17.356 --> 00:55:20.193
No one's lost a thumb for
at least the last ten years.

822
00:55:20.276 --> 00:55:23.196
- He could be from anywhere.
- I can't access all that.

823
00:55:23.279 --> 00:55:24.614
Forget the files.

824
00:55:24.697 --> 00:55:26.908
I want you to start going
through the pension fund.

825
00:55:26.991 --> 00:55:28.367
This guy's drawin' disability.

826
00:55:28.451 --> 00:55:30.703
He may not be LAPD,
but he's livin' here now.

827
00:55:30.786 --> 00:55:31.829
I want pictures!

828
00:55:32.497 --> 00:55:34.165
I've seen this asshole.

829
00:55:35.458 --> 00:55:38.461
(HORN HONKING)

830
00:55:48.304 --> 00:55:49.972
- Hey!
- Hey, Mac!

831
00:55:50.056 --> 00:55:53.226
- Let's get these passengers off the bus!
- We can't do it, sir.

832
00:55:53.309 --> 00:55:55.102
There's no time for any stunts, Traven.

833
00:55:55.186 --> 00:55:56.938
We gotta get these
people out of harm's way.

834
00:55:57.021 --> 00:55:58.064
I got orders!

835
00:55:58.147 --> 00:56:00.316
We move these people, he'll see.

836
00:56:02.818 --> 00:56:05.238
Remember... crazy, not stupid.

837
00:56:05.363 --> 00:56:08.198
All right, look, Harry's tr
yin' to find out who this guy is.

838
00:56:08.282 --> 00:56:11.076
- We think maybe he's a cop.
- NORWOOD (OVER RADIO): <i>Lieutenant!</i>

839
00:56:11.160 --> 00:56:14.455
It's him. He wants to talk to Jack.

840
00:56:14.789 --> 00:56:18.084
- He's on the line for you.
- Okay, give him the number.

841
00:56:18.501 --> 00:56:19.961
Give him the number!

842
00:56:22.380 --> 00:56:24.966
- How's he doing?
- The bleeding is less, but...

843
00:56:25.049 --> 00:56:26.509
Are they going to help us?

844
00:56:26.634 --> 00:56:28.469
Sure they are. They're the police.

845
00:56:28.761 --> 00:56:31.222
Hey, your taxes are pa yin' their salary.

846
00:56:31.430 --> 00:56:33.558
If we die, they gotta take a pay cut.

847
00:56:33.724 --> 00:56:34.976
(COUGHS)

848
00:56:36.394 --> 00:56:39.397
I mean, you know... (CELL PHONE RINGS)

849
00:56:41.649 --> 00:56:43.859
- Yeah.
- BOMBER: <i>I think we have trust.</i>

850
00:56:44.110 --> 00:56:48.531
But it looks on TV like you're tr yin'
to get those passengers off the bus.

851
00:56:48.614 --> 00:56:50.199
Look, you gotta let me have one.

852
00:56:50.283 --> 00:56:51.784
<i>Now, we went over the rules.</i>

853
00:56:51.867 --> 00:56:53.119
As an act of faith.

854
00:56:53.202 --> 00:56:55.913
We have an injured man
here. The driver's been shot.

855
00:56:56.038 --> 00:56:58.791
Jack, now tell me that you haven't
been shooting the passengers.

856
00:56:58.874 --> 00:57:01.377
I thought it was customary
for a police officer

857
00:57:01.460 --> 00:57:03.921
