968
01:02:56.357 --> 01:03:00.194
Fuck. You're fired!
Everybody's fuckin' fired!

969
01:03:01.612 --> 01:03:03.072
Get me closer!

970
01:03:03.948 --> 01:03:06.075
Hey, get closer. Watch him in the mirror.

971
01:03:07.451 --> 01:03:08.452
Jack!

972
01:03:11.830 --> 01:03:15.501
- How big is the section?
- Fifty feet. At least.

973
01:03:20.839 --> 01:03:24.093
There's a gap in the
road up ahead. It's big.

974
01:03:24.259 --> 01:03:26.595
You're kidding. How big?

975
01:03:26.679 --> 01:03:29.765
- MAC: Fifty feet. Jack.
- What?

976
01:03:29.890 --> 01:03:32.768
We gotta get these people
off the bus somehow.

977
01:03:32.851 --> 01:03:35.604
- You know I can't.
- (HELICOPTER FLYING BY)

978
01:03:35.688 --> 01:03:39.108
ANNIE: What did... What did he say? Jack?

979
01:03:39.650 --> 01:03:42.194
Jack, what'd he say?

980
01:03:43.654 --> 01:03:45.072
What's the matter?

981
01:03:50.911 --> 01:03:53.205
- There's a gap in the freeway.
- What?

982
01:03:53.372 --> 01:03:55.124
(PASSENGERS GASPING, MURMURING)

983
01:03:55.207 --> 01:03:57.668
- What do you mean?
- How big is a gap?

984
01:03:58.168 --> 01:04:01.213
Fifty feet. A couple of miles ahead.

985
01:04:01.296 --> 01:04:04.508
- This is crazy.
- Right along up there?

986
01:04:06.760 --> 01:04:08.846
- What is this?
- Geez.

987
01:04:08.929 --> 01:04:11.557
Jack! Jack!

988
01:04:11.640 --> 01:04:14.226
What if I shift into neutral and
just keep the engine revving?

989
01:04:14.309 --> 01:04:15.436
No, he'd have thought of that.

990
01:04:15.519 --> 01:04:16.895
Then what then? What? What?

991
01:04:18.689 --> 01:04:21.900
- What? Jack!
- Floor it.

992
01:04:21.984 --> 01:04:23.777
- What?
- Floor it!

993
01:04:23.861 --> 01:04:25.904
It's an interchange.
There might be an incline.

994
01:04:25.988 --> 01:04:27.239
- Floor it!
- Fine.

995
01:04:31.076 --> 01:04:34.038
Everybody, hold onto your
seats or whatever you can.

996
01:04:34.872 --> 01:04:37.750
When we hit the gap, heads down.

997
01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:40.335
That's it? That's it?

998
01:04:40.419 --> 01:04:42.046
That's all we can do.

999
01:04:42.504 --> 01:04:44.854
Let's put these underneath
your seat, all right?

1000
01:04:45.549 --> 01:04:47.634
Put your bags underneath the seat.

1001
01:04:52.556 --> 01:04:54.725
Hey, I didn't mean to shoot the guy.

1002
01:04:55.184 --> 01:04:56.477
Hold on.

1003
01:04:57.478 --> 01:04:58.896
Is this really gonna work?

1004
01:05:00.397 --> 01:05:01.732
ANNIE: Jack!

1005
01:05:03.358 --> 01:05:04.359
Yeah.

1006
01:05:05.903 --> 01:05:06.904
Jack.

1007
01:05:28.634 --> 01:05:30.593
- Come on, come on, come on.
- ANNIE: Oh, God.

1008
01:05:30.677 --> 01:05:32.137
- JACK: Come on, come on.
- ANNIE: God.

1009
01:05:32.221 --> 01:05:34.223
- Come on!
- Oh, God.

1010
01:05:43.690 --> 01:05:44.900
MAC: Oh, shit.

1011
01:05:58.413 --> 01:06:01.125
- Everybody, hold on!
- (WHIMPERING)

1012
01:06:13.804 --> 01:06:15.848
(CRYING) I wanna see our baby.

1013
01:06:18.225 --> 01:06:20.435
Oh, God. Jack.

1014
01:06:26.316 --> 01:06:27.359
ANNIE: Shit!

1015
01:06:37.661 --> 01:06:39.121
(PASSENGERS SCREAMING)

1016
01:06:41.707 --> 01:06:43.709
(PASSENGERS GASPING, SCREAMING)

1017
01:06:47.462 --> 01:06:49.006
ANNIE: Okay. Okay.

1018
01:06:49.882 --> 01:06:51.049
Yes!

1019
01:06:52.634 --> 01:06:55.220
- We are way out of control!
- We made it!

1020
01:07:02.060 --> 01:07:05.022
- You okay? You okay?
- Yeah. I'm okay. I'm okay.

1021
01:07:05.189 --> 01:07:08.442
All right! All right! Let's go!

1022
01:07:08.525 --> 01:07:11.403
- Is everybody okay?
- Yes! Yes!

1023
01:07:11.486 --> 01:07:12.946
(LAUGHING)

1024
01:07:14.489 --> 01:07:17.326
- ORTIZ: We made it!
- We made it.

1025
01:07:18.785 --> 01:07:21.622
You are the man. You are the man!

1026
01:07:21.705 --> 01:07:23.665
Thank you. Thank you very much.

1027
01:07:23.749 --> 01:07:25.417
ORTIZ: Goddamn! Yes!

1028
01:07:26.793 --> 01:07:29.004
- Oh, shit.
- I think you missed your calling.

1029
01:07:29.087 --> 01:07:30.505
Yeah? What was it?

1030
01:07:32.090 --> 01:07:34.885
Watch the road. You
should've been a pilot.

1031
01:07:35.010 --> 01:07:38.347
Ow. (GROANS)

1032
01:07:40.891 --> 01:07:43.352
- Jesus.
- Get off!

1033
01:07:43.518 --> 01:07:45.479
- What?
- Get off this.

1034
01:07:45.562 --> 01:07:47.147
Now, now! Get off this!

1035
01:07:52.361 --> 01:07:53.612
In there.

1036
01:07:53.987 --> 01:07:55.948
- Where, right here?
- Yeah.

1037
01:07:56.031 --> 01:07:57.532
- Right here?
- Yeah.

1038
01:07:57.616 --> 01:07:58.992
(PASSENGERS SCREAMING)

1039
01:07:59.076 --> 01:08:01.411
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1040
01:08:01.495 --> 01:08:04.206
Hey. Hey, hey, stop! Stop!

1041
01:08:13.674 --> 01:08:15.842
- He's just entered the airport.
- MAC: All right!

1042
01:08:15.926 --> 01:08:18.470
- There's thousands of people there.
- That's my boy, Jack.

1043
01:08:18.553 --> 01:08:20.680
He should be able to circle the
runways and buy us some time.

1044
01:08:20.764 --> 01:08:23.600
The choppers can't fly in
there. It's restricted airspace.

1045
01:08:23.684 --> 01:08:25.018
He's headed for the end of the field.

1046
01:08:25.102 --> 01:08:28.021
That must be Bravo Tango,
an emergency runway.

1047
01:08:28.105 --> 01:08:30.105
Yeah, let's hope it's built. Let's move!

1048
01:08:43.078 --> 01:08:44.579
We're at the airport.

1049
01:08:45.831 --> 01:08:47.249
Yeah. So?

1050
01:08:48.917 --> 01:08:50.669
I already seen the airport.

1051
01:08:57.718 --> 01:09:00.470
(SIRENS WAILING)

1052
01:09:08.562 --> 01:09:09.896
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1053
01:09:11.732 --> 01:09:12.858
Yeah?

1054
01:09:13.025 --> 01:09:15.777
Very, very exciting, Jack.

1055
01:09:15.861 --> 01:09:17.863
Some close calls, huh?

1056
01:09:17.988 --> 01:09:20.073
But you've done all right for yourself.

1057
01:09:20.157 --> 01:09:21.325
What do you want?

1058
01:09:21.408 --> 01:09:23.118
I want money, Jack.

1059
01:09:23.452 --> 01:09:26.163
I wish, uh, that I had
some loftier purpose,

1060
01:09:26.246 --> 01:09:29.416
but, um, I'm afraid in the
end it's just the money, Jack.

1061
01:09:29.791 --> 01:09:33.962
I would like, uh, large,
uh, non-sequential bills

1062
01:09:34.046 --> 01:09:36.923
in two clear plastic bags, unmarked.

1063
01:09:37.007 --> 01:09:38.675
Can you remember all that?

1064
01:09:39.343 --> 01:09:40.844
What are you telling me for?

1065
01:09:42.346 --> 01:09:44.139
Because I want you to help
me to get it before it gets too late.

1066
01:09:44.222 --> 01:09:46.099
I hate negotiators, Jack.

1067
01:09:46.183 --> 01:09:48.101
They talk to you like
they're your best friend,

1068
01:09:48.185 --> 01:09:49.853
and they don't even know ya.

1069
01:09:50.228 --> 01:09:52.773
Why are they messing with me, huh?

1070
01:09:52.856 --> 01:09:54.900
Do they think I'm doin' this for fun?

1071
01:09:55.067 --> 01:09:58.320
- Aren't you?
<i>- Oh, that's unfair, Jack.</i>

1072
01:09:58.487 --> 01:10:00.906
You don't know how I feel about this.

1073
01:10:01.406 --> 01:10:02.908
You don't even know me.

1074
01:10:03.033 --> 01:10:05.493
I know you want a shitload
of money you didn't earn.

1075
01:10:05.577 --> 01:10:06.745
Oh, I earned it.

1076
01:10:07.579 --> 01:10:09.956
I spent my life earning it.

1077
01:10:10.123 --> 01:10:11.792
<i>I got a medal, too, Jack.</i>

1078
01:10:11.875 --> 01:10:15.629
<i>A medal and a pink slip
and a "sorry about your hand."</i>

1079
01:10:15.712 --> 01:10:17.255
You have to let me off.

1080
01:10:17.381 --> 01:10:20.550
Oh, no! That's not good.

1081
01:10:20.675 --> 01:10:22.052
You want me to help you?

1082
01:10:22.135 --> 01:10:23.804
I need to talk to these
people face-to-face.

1083
01:10:23.887 --> 01:10:25.597
They think you're bullshit.

1084
01:10:26.056 --> 01:10:27.974
They don't think that.

1085
01:10:28.058 --> 01:10:30.560
Look, you want the money, I
don't want anyone else to die.

1086
01:10:30.644 --> 01:10:32.437
Let me get on the ground.

1087
01:10:32.729 --> 01:10:35.857
Just me. That's not against the rules.

1088
01:10:36.066 --> 01:10:38.193
All right. I want you back real fast.

1089
01:10:39.277 --> 01:10:40.362
Fine.

1090
01:10:40.904 --> 01:10:43.073
<i>Jack, nothing tricky now.</i>

1091
01:10:43.156 --> 01:10:44.741
<i>You know that I'm on top of you.</i>

1092
01:10:44.825 --> 01:10:47.494
Do not attempt to grow a brain.

1093
01:10:48.703 --> 01:10:50.038
MAN (ON TV): <i>It could
encourage other terrorists</i>

1094
01:10:50.122 --> 01:10:51.622
<i>to try and pull off another...</i>

1095
01:10:56.586 --> 01:10:58.672
So, I guess there's a plan now?

1096
01:10:58.880 --> 01:11:00.048
Could be.

1097
01:11:00.674 --> 01:11:02.676
- Yeah?
- He's letting me off.

1098
01:11:02.843 --> 01:11:03.927
What?

1099
01:11:04.136 --> 01:11:05.886
Just keep circling. You'll be fine.

1100
01:11:08.014 --> 01:11:10.350
Everybody, sit tight. I'm
getting off for a minute.

1101
01:11:10.434 --> 01:11:12.727
- Do you think that's a good idea?
- It'll be okay.

1102
01:11:12.811 --> 01:11:15.689
- What, are you just gonna leave us here?
- I would.

1103
01:11:15.897 --> 01:11:18.066
Don't worry. I won't go far.

1104
01:11:18.150 --> 01:11:19.234
ANNIE: Hey.

1105
01:11:20.610 --> 01:11:21.710
Don't forget about us.

1106
01:11:36.877 --> 01:11:38.211
The choppers are gone, Jack.

1107
01:11:38.295 --> 01:11:40.839
- Let's dump the passengers now.
- No way. He's ready for that.

1108
01:11:40.922 --> 01:11:42.299
How is that possible?

1109
01:11:42.466 --> 01:11:44.301
I don't know how, Mac. I just know he is.

1110
01:11:44.384 --> 01:11:46.261
He's been a step ahead every time.

1111
01:11:46.344 --> 01:11:48.054
If we unload, he'll take
them out, I guarantee.

1112
01:11:48.138 --> 01:11:50.140
So where does that put us?

1113
01:11:50.223 --> 01:11:52.123
I have to try and dismantle that bomb.

1114
01:11:52.225 --> 01:11:55.061
REPORTER: That's an
incredible ride... the 10 Freeway,

1115
01:11:55.145 --> 01:11:57.731
leaving Los Angeles to the 105 Freeway,

1116
01:11:57.814 --> 01:12:01.151
this Santa Monica bus has ended up
here at Los Angeles International Airport,

1117
01:12:01.234 --> 01:12:02.777
circling the runway.

1118
01:12:14.915 --> 01:12:17.709
I'm tellin' ya, honey,
he's somewhere jerkin' off.

1119
01:12:17.792 --> 01:12:20.795
He didn't have to get on the
bus in the first place, Ortiz.

1120
01:12:21.713 --> 01:12:23.840
Hey, get your ass behind the yellow line.

1121
01:12:27.219 --> 01:12:28.512
What is that?

1122
01:12:33.141 --> 01:12:34.935
ANNIE: I have no idea.

1123
01:12:38.480 --> 01:12:41.024
We won't be able to hold
this thing steady for very long.

1124
01:12:41.107 --> 01:12:42.609
I just need a few minutes.

1125
01:12:42.692 --> 01:12:44.992
If I can't do it by
then, I can't do it at all.

1126
01:12:45.487 --> 01:12:47.405
Harry, you with me?

1127
01:12:47.489 --> 01:12:49.789
HARRY (OVER RADIO):
<i>Yeah. You be careful, Jack.</i>

1128
01:12:53.662 --> 01:12:54.955
What is he doing?

1129
01:12:55.580 --> 01:12:57.666
Oh, my God, he is insane.

1130
01:13:03.713 --> 01:13:07.551
Okay, Jack, this is it. Don't get dead.

1131
01:13:10.512 --> 01:13:13.890
(CREAKING)

1132
01:13:21.731 --> 01:13:23.316
This is not a very good plan.

1133
01:13:23.400 --> 01:13:24.526
Have faith, sister.

1134
01:13:24.609 --> 01:13:25.610
Oh, Christ.

1135
01:13:36.162 --> 01:13:38.290
Just keep it steady.

1136
01:13:38.373 --> 01:13:40.292
Oh, thank you for the tip, Ortiz.

1137
01:13:52.512 --> 01:13:53.930
This guy is nuts!

1138
01:13:54.014 --> 01:13:55.515
Gosh darn.

1139
01:13:55.849 --> 01:13:59.060
Okay, we're gonna have to try to bypass
the remote current with the battery.

1140
01:13:59.144 --> 01:14:01.020
Can you find the trip
wire for the remote?

1141
01:14:01.104 --> 01:14:03.273
I don't know. I got a few choices here.

1142
01:14:03.565 --> 01:14:06.484
<i>- Black and red?</i>
- And green.

1143
01:14:06.693 --> 01:14:07.736
Okay.

1144
01:14:08.028 --> 01:14:09.487
All right. I'm gonna guess he's not gonna

1145
01:14:09.571 --> 01:14:11.197
go with standard copper for the remote.

1146
01:14:11.281 --> 01:14:13.408
That'd be too weak.
I'd use a fiber alloy.

1147
01:14:13.575 --> 01:14:16.661
<i>Uh, Jack, I'm gonna need
you to look at the wire.</i>

1148
01:14:18.872 --> 01:14:20.915
- Harry, it's covered.
- Yeah, I know.

1149
01:14:20.999 --> 01:14:22.334
You're gonna have to cut off the sheath.

1150
01:14:22.417 --> 01:14:24.085
But don't cut the wire.

1151
01:14:24.294 --> 01:14:25.754
Right.

1152
01:14:38.892 --> 01:14:40.518
- (TIRES SCREECHING)
- Fuck me!

1153
01:14:42.270 --> 01:14:43.271
JACK: <i>Shit!</i>

1154
01:14:49.194 --> 01:14:50.695
- Bull's-eye!
- HARRY: <i>Great.</i>

1155
01:14:50.904 --> 01:14:54.449
Okay, I want you to clip on the
battery and then run it to the lead wire.

1156
01:14:54.532 --> 01:14:55.533
JACK: <i>Copy.</i>

1157
01:15:10.090 --> 01:15:11.091
(BEEPS)

1158
01:15:12.634 --> 01:15:14.803
I can't bypass. It'll fire.

1159
01:15:14.928 --> 01:15:16.971
Oh, shit! It's a collapsible circuit.

1160
01:15:18.515 --> 01:15:22.227
WOMAN: "Howard Payne,
Atlanta PD bomb squad."

1161
01:15:22.352 --> 01:15:24.521
"Retired in Sun Valley in 1989"

1162
01:15:24.604 --> 01:15:27.899
"when a small charge left him
with fingers numbering nine."

1163
01:15:27.982 --> 01:15:29.526
That's our scumbag!

1164
01:15:29.609 --> 01:15:31.236
We got him. Jack, we found him.

1165
01:15:31.319 --> 01:15:33.029
We can get to his place
inside of 15 minutes.

1166
01:15:33.113 --> 01:15:35.365
Great. Jack, I want you to
get out of there and sit tight.

1167
01:15:35.448 --> 01:15:36.741
We're gonna go after the source.

1168
01:15:36.825 --> 01:15:37.992
Watch your back.

1169
01:15:39.786 --> 01:15:41.121
Wait, wait, wait for me!

1170
01:15:41.287 --> 01:15:43.164
Mac, get me out of here.

1171
01:15:44.416 --> 01:15:45.916
- (GRUNTS)
- (TIRES SCREECHING)

1172
01:15:56.594 --> 01:16:00.044
Somebody go to the back and check
and see if he came out the back! Go!

1173
01:16:06.896 --> 01:16:08.606
(GRUNTING)

1174
01:16:11.943 --> 01:16:14.362
- ANNIE: Can you see him?
- He's not behind us!

1175
01:16:14.571 --> 01:16:16.531
- What?
- He's not back here!

1176
01:16:16.698 --> 01:16:19.743
Oh, my God! Go look! Lay
down and look under the bus

1177
01:16:19.826 --> 01:16:21.726
and see if you can see him down there.

1178
01:16:23.621 --> 01:16:25.206
- ANNIE: Can you see him?
- No!

1179
01:16:25.290 --> 01:16:28.376
You don't see him,
like, back by the tires?

1180
01:16:28.501 --> 01:16:30.545
- I can't see him!
- Are you sure?

1181
01:16:30.628 --> 01:16:32.130
I can't see him!

1182
01:16:54.569 --> 01:16:56.362
- Oh my God, we hit him!
- What the hell was that?

1183
01:16:56.446 --> 01:16:58.823
- Oh, my God! Do you see him?
- Did we hit him?

1184
01:16:58.907 --> 01:17:01.607
Look out the side of the
window and see the other side!

1185
01:17:04.120 --> 01:17:05.121
(GRUNTING)

1186
01:17:08.541 --> 01:17:11.169
- My tools!
- Will somebody get him his tools?

1187
01:17:23.431 --> 01:17:25.558
Please help him! Hurry!

1188
01:17:27.060 --> 01:17:29.729
God, we're dragging him. Do you see him?

1189
01:17:29.938 --> 01:17:31.981
Where is he? Is he there?

1190
01:17:34.108 --> 01:17:35.360
ANNIE: Do you see him?

1191
01:17:35.527 --> 01:17:38.238
- Jack!
- Jack!

1192
01:17:38.446 --> 01:17:40.657
- I see him!
- What?

1193
01:17:40.740 --> 01:17:42.867
- I see him!
- You do? Is he okay?

1194
01:17:42.951 --> 01:17:45.286
He's all right! He's all right!

1195
01:17:45.370 --> 01:17:46.746
Yeah! Whoo! Whoo!

1196
01:17:46.830 --> 01:17:48.748
Hold my legs! Hold my legs!

1197
01:17:48.832 --> 01:17:50.333
Somebody, hold my legs!

1198
01:17:50.416 --> 01:17:51.793
Hold his legs!

1199
01:17:52.502 --> 01:17:53.503
Hold his legs!

1200
01:17:53.586 --> 01:17:54.629
ORTIZ: Come on!

1201
01:17:56.548 --> 01:17:59.175
Come on! I got ya!

1202
01:18:00.885 --> 01:18:03.304
(GROANING)

1203
01:18:03.429 --> 01:18:05.098
Is he hurt? Is he okay?

1204
01:18:05.181 --> 01:18:08.059
ORTIZ: Pull! Pull!

1205
01:18:08.142 --> 01:18:10.270
Come on! Come on!

1206
01:18:10.353 --> 01:18:12.689
We got him now! Come on, pull!

1207
01:18:13.773 --> 01:18:15.733
Jesus, I can't believe it. (LAUGHS)

1208
01:18:18.278 --> 01:18:19.821
You are a complete jerk!

1209
01:18:19.946 --> 01:18:22.740
- You know that?
- WOMAN: Oh, thank God!

1210
01:18:22.866 --> 01:18:24.533
Did you have any luck with the bomb?

1211
01:18:24.617 --> 01:18:26.035
Yeah. It didn't go off.

1212
01:18:28.079 --> 01:18:29.247
JACK: Ortiz, thanks.

1213
01:18:29.372 --> 01:18:31.416
How many lives you got, man?

1214
01:18:33.126 --> 01:18:34.826
ORTIZ: You're not too bright, man,

1215
01:18:35.378 --> 01:18:39.716
but you got some big, round,
hairy <i>cojones.</i> (LAUGHING)

1216
01:18:40.008 --> 01:18:43.761
That's... very gross, Ortiz.

1217
01:18:45.054 --> 01:18:46.764
Can't even pay him a compliment.

1218
01:18:48.474 --> 01:18:50.977
- How you doin'?
- You scared the shit out of me, Jack!

1219
01:18:51.060 --> 01:18:52.061
Ow.

1220
01:18:52.145 --> 01:18:53.479
Other than that, I'm fine.

1221
01:18:54.272 --> 01:18:55.648
What is that smell?

1222
01:18:56.274 --> 01:18:58.860
- It's gas.
- We're leaking gas?

1223
01:18:58.985 --> 01:19:00.278
We are now.

1224
01:19:04.824 --> 01:19:07.535
What, you thought you needed
another challenge or something?

1225
01:19:07.619 --> 01:19:10.371
- Mac.
<i>- Mac here. Go ahead.</i>

1226
01:19:10.663 --> 01:19:12.248
Can you get a fuel truck to pace us here?

1227
01:19:12.332 --> 01:19:13.458
We're losing gas.

1228
01:19:13.541 --> 01:19:15.001
I'll see what I can find.

1229
01:19:15.084 --> 01:19:17.284
- How much time?
- I don't know. Ten minutes.

1230
01:19:17.378 --> 01:19:19.881
- It doesn't look good.
- Got ya.

1231
01:19:19.964 --> 01:19:21.674
Norwood, get a fuel car out here.

1232
